24/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The defence ministers and army chiefs of staff of Albania, Macedonia and Bulgaria are meeting in Sofia on Friday (24 September). 
The two-day session will be dedicated to army reforms, with Bulgaria sharing its experiences on the road to NATO membership. 
The military leaders will also talk about organising possible joint military exercises, as well as the possible extension of co-operation between intelligence services. 
Such meetings are expected to continue on a regular basis, with Romania joining later. 
(Novinite, Makfax, news.bg - 24/09/04)
